'From Squeak3.1alpha of 4 February 2001 [latest update: #3773] on 3 March 2001 at 8:44:07 pm'!"Change Set:		Misc-arDate:			3 March 2001Author:			Andreas RaabThree different fixes. Allow PaintInvoking morphs to be dropped into parts bin without invoking paint.Make status controls update themselves accordingly.Allow ViewerFlapTabs to be hibernated even if not universal tiles."!!PaintInvokingMorph methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'ar 3/3/2001 20:41'!justDroppedInto: aPasteUpMorph event: anEvent	"This message is sent to a dropped morph after it has been dropped on--and been accepted by--a drop-sensitive morph"	aPasteUpMorph isPartsBin ifFalse:[		self delete.		^aPasteUpMorph makeNewDrawing: anEvent].	^super justDroppedInto: aPasteUpMorph event: anEvent! !!PaintInvokingMorph methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'ar 3/3/2001 20:40'!wantsToBeDroppedInto: aMorph	"Only into PasteUps that are not part bins"	^aMorph isPlayfieldLike! !!ScriptStatusControl methodsFor: 'initialization' stamp: 'ar 3/3/2001 20:34'!intoWorld: aWorld	super intoWorld: aWorld.	aWorld ifNotNil:[self updateStatus].! !!ScriptStatusControl methodsFor: 'access' stamp: 'ar 3/3/2001 20:32'!updateStatus	scriptInstantiation updateStatusMorph: self! !!ViewerFlapTab methodsFor: 'as yet unclassified' stamp: 'ar 3/3/2001 20:24'!hibernate	"drop my viewer to save space when writing to the disk."	referent submorphs do: 		[:m | (m isKindOf: Viewer) ifTrue: [m delete]]! !